main event: A bright starlike object was sighted over the Pacific Ocean on November 29, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed rising from the horizon to a high altitude, moving in a course of 240 degrees.
The object emitted an aurora-like light.
The sighting was reported by ships in the Pacific Ocean at coordinates 33N 143E.
The report was part of Project Blue Book, the U.S. Air Force's official investigation of UFOs.
Copies of the report were delivered to the Defense Intelligence Agency and other agencies.
